.TH LVIBE 1 "2026" "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lvibe \- Lé Vibe launcher (managed Ollama + Code OSS editor)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lvibe
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ editor_args " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Same program as
.BR le\-vibe (1).
Launches the Lé Vibe session: optional product first\-run bootstrap,
starts a dedicated\-port \fBollama serve\fR, then your editor (defaults in
\fBle_vibe.launcher\fR: \fBLE_VIBE_EDITOR\fR if set, else \fB/usr/lib/le-vibe/bin/codium\fR,
else \fB/usr/bin/codium\fR, else \fBcodium\fR on \fBPATH\fR). On exit, stops the
managed Ollama process so GPU VRAM is released.
.PP
Open the current project in the editor:
.B lvibe \.
.PP
Product naming: Lé Vibe is not Microsoft Visual Studio Code; use Code \-
OSS / VSCodium\-class editors.
.PP
After successful first\-run, the launcher may run \fBle\-vibe\-setup\-continue\fR automatically (pinned Continue + YAML extensions and \fB~/.continue/config.yaml\fR sync; \fBdocs/continue\-extension\-pin.md\fR). Set \fBLE_VIBE_AUTO_CONTINUE_SETUP=0\fR to disable.
.PP
When first\-run bootstrap fails: set \fBLE_VIBE_VERBOSE\fR for stderr detail; \fBlvibe logs\fR prints the path and a \fBtail \-f\fR reminder, or use \fBlvibe logs \-\-path\-only\fR / \fBlvibe logs \-\-tail\fR \fIN\fR (STEP 6). \fBlvibe \-\-help\fR lists the same remediation flags (\fB\-\-skip\-first\-run\fR, \fB\-\-force\-first\-run\fR, \fBLE_VIBE_VERBOSE\fR, \fBlvibe logs\fR; STEP 6). Same story as \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) OPTIONS; see \fBle\-vibe/README.md\fR \fIFirst\-run (launcher)\fR and \fBPRODUCT_SPEC_SECTION8_EVIDENCE.md\fR §10.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lvibe sync-agent-skills
.RI [ workspace ]
Copy missing agent skill templates into \fB.lvibe/agents/<agent_id>/skill.md\fR (e.g. after upgrading the \fBle\-vibe\fR stack). \fIworkspace\fR defaults to the current directory; \fB.lvibe/\fR must already exist. Does not start Ollama or the editor.
.TP
.B lvibe open-welcome
.RI [ workspace ]
Open \fB.lvibe/WELCOME.md\fR (PRODUCT_SPEC §4) in the editor. \fIworkspace\fR defaults to the current directory; \fB.lvibe/\fR must already exist from a prior consent\-gated open. Does not start Ollama or first\-run bootstrap.
.TP
.B lvibe welcome
.RI [ \-\-text " " workspace ]
Print path to \fB.lvibe/WELCOME.md\fR or \fB\-\-text\fR for full §4 copy (terminal). STEP 4 / E3.
.TP
.B lvibe apply\-opening\-skip
.RI [ workspace ]
Advance \fBsession\-manifest.json\fR when \fBmeta.current_step_id\fR is \fBopening_intent\fR (skip hook). \fBdocs/SESSION_ORCHESTRATION_SPEC.md\fR STEP 2.
.TP
.B lvibe continue\-rules
.RI [ workspace ]
Seed \fB.continue/rules/*.md\fR so Chat/Agent treats \fB.lvibe/\fR as primary memory (STEP 3 / E2). Idempotent.
.TP
.B lvibe hygiene
.RI [ hygiene_options ]
Validate \fB.lvibe/\fR manifest, session JSON, \fBstorage\-state.json\fR (if present), chunk path refs — \fB\-\-json\fR for machine output. Same as \fBpython3 \-m le_vibe.hygiene\fR and \fBlvibe\-hygiene\fR(1). See \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) for the stack install.
.TP
.B lvibe workspace\-governance
.RI [ \-C " dir " | \-\-json ]
§5 consent, storage cap, \fB.lvibe/\fR usage vs cap — \fBPRODUCT_SPEC\fR §5; \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 15.
.TP
.B lvibe master\-orchestrator
.RI [ \-\-print | \-\-json ]
\fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 16 — paths to queue docs; \fB\-\-print\fR emits fenced Master prompt (same as \fBprint\-master\-orchestrator\-prompt.py\fR).
.TP
.B lvibe ai\-pilot\-continue
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json ]
\fBdocs/AI_PILOT_AND_CONTINUE.md\fR STEP 17 — scope doc, Continue rules, root \fBREADME\fR; \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths.
.TP
.B lvibe logs
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-tail " N " | \-\-json ]
With no flags: print the structured log path (\fB~/.config/le\-vibe/le\-vibe.log.jsonl\fR) and a \fBtail \-f\fR reminder. With \fB\-\-path\-only\fR, \fB\-\-tail\fR \fIN\fR, or \fB\-\-json\fR: path only, last \fIN\fR lines, or metadata. Local JSON Lines only — \fBdocs/privacy\-and\-telemetry.md\fR.
.TP
.B lvibe continue-pin
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-json ]
Print the pinned Open VSX semver for Continue (\fBcontinue.continue@\fIver\fR), path only, or JSON (\fBpin_file\fR, \fBsemver\fR, \fBopenvsx_id\fR). Pin file: \fB/usr/share/le\-vibe/continue\-openvsx\-version\fR when installed, else monorepo \fBpackaging/continue\-openvsx\-version\fR; \fBLE_VIBE_CONTINUE_PIN_FILE\fR overrides. \fBdocs/continue\-extension\-pin.md\fR.
.TP
.B lvibe verify-checksums
.RI [ \-C " dir " | \-\-json ]
Run \fBsha256sum \-c SHA256SUMS\fR in a release directory (artifact extract); \fB\-\-json\fR prints paths, exit code, and captured output. \fBdocs/apt\-repo\-releases.md\fR (H1).
.TP
.B lvibe pip-audit
.RI [ \-\-json | pip\-audit_options ]
Run \fBpip\-audit \-r\fR against \fBle\-vibe/requirements.txt\fR in a git clone (\fBpip install pip\-audit\fR); \fB\-\-json\fR prints paths, exit code, and captured output. Not available when the stack \fB.deb\fR omits \fBrequirements.txt\fR — \fBdocs/sbom\-signing\-audit.md\fR (H2).
.TP
.B lvibe ci-smoke
.RI [ \-\-json | args ]
Run \fBpackaging/scripts/ci\-smoke.sh\fR from the monorepo root (\fBLE_VIBE_REPO_ROOT\fR or parent walk); \fB\-\-json\fR prints paths, exit code, and captured output. \fBdocs/ci\-qa\-hardening.md\fR (H3).
.TP
.B lvibe ci\-editor\-gate
.RI [ \-\-json | args ]
Run \fBpackaging/scripts/ci\-editor\-gate.sh\fR (same as \fB./editor/smoke.sh\fR gate); \fB\-\-json\fR prints paths, exit code, and captured output. \fBdocs/ci\-qa\-hardening.md\fR (H3).
.TP
.B lvibe brand-paths
.RI [ \-\-path\-only | \-\-json ]
Print paths to canonical \fBle\-vibe.svg\fR (monorepo \fBpackaging/icons/...\fR and/or \fB/usr/share/icons/...\fR when installed); \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths. \fBdocs/brand\-assets.md\fR (H5).
.TP
.B lvibe product\-surface
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json ]
List \fB.github/\fR CI, Dependabot, issue \fBconfig.yml\fR, \fBdocs/README.md\fR, privacy, \fBSECURITY.md\fR; \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths. \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 12 (H8).
.TP
.B lvibe flatpak\-appimage
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json ]
List \fBdocs/flatpak\-appimage.md\fR, \fBpackaging/flatpak/\fR manifest, \fBpackaging/appimage/\fR scripts; \fB\-\-json\fR for structured paths. \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 13 (H7).
.TP
.B lvibe ide\-prereqs
.RI [ \-\-path\-only " KEY " | \-\-json | \-\-print\-closeout\-commands ]
§7.3 IDE \fB.deb\fR paths and \fBeditor/vscodium\fR tree state (ready / partial / absent); \fB\-\-json\fR includes \fBvscode_linux_build\fR (ready / partial / absent), \fBvscode_linux_ready\fR, \fBvscode_linux_partial\fR, \fBhicolor_icon_in_deb\fR (newest \fBpackaging/le\-vibe\-ide\fR \fB.deb\fR — same \fBdpkg\-deb \-\-contents\fR check as \fBpreflight\-step14\-closeout.sh\fR / \fBverify\-step14\-closeout.sh\fR), \fBstatic_prereq_files_ok\fR, \fBvscodium_linux_svg_staged\fR, per\-path \fBentries\fR, and paths. \fB\-\-print\-closeout\-commands\fR prints \fBpackaging/scripts/probe\-vscode\-linux\-build.sh\fR (same classifier), \fBpackaging/scripts/probe\_vscode\_linux\_build.py \-h\fR (same recovery text as shell \fB\-\-help\fR), \fBpackaging/scripts/preflight\-step14\-closeout.sh\fR (\fB\-\-json\fR: structured gap summary on stdout) and \fBverify\-step14\-closeout.sh\fR\, \fBgit \-C editor/vscodium checkout \-\- .\fR (tracked drift after §7.3 prepare — \fBeditor/BUILD.md\fR submodule restore)\, then status\-specific lines (submodule bootstrap, toolchain + \fBdev/build.sh\fR, or \fBpackaging/scripts/build\-le\-vibe\-debs.sh \-\-with\-ide\fR when \fBbin/codium\fR exists; \fB\-\-with\-ide\fR exits before stack \fBdpkg\-buildpackage\fR when the probe is not \fBready\fR; \fBpartial\fR / \fBabsent\fR: \fBpackaging/scripts/trigger\-le\-vibe\-ide\-linux\-compile.sh\fR (\fBworkflow_dispatch\fR \fBlinux_compile\fR), \fBpackaging/scripts/download\-vscodium\-linux\-compile\-artifact.sh\fR (\fB\-\-install\fR), \fBpackaging/scripts/print\-github\-linux\-compile\-artifact\-hint.sh\fR for CI \fBlinux_compile\fR tarball, then \fBpackaging/scripts/install\-vscodium\-linux\-tarball\-to\-editor\-vendor.sh\fR; \fBpackaging/scripts/print\-step14\-vscode\-linux\-bin\-files.sh\fR (same \fBbin/\fR list as \fB\-\-json\fR), \fBeditor/print\-ci\-tarball\-codium\-path.sh\fR (temp unpack) — \fBeditor/BUILD.md\fR 14.f); \fBpackaging/scripts/verify\-step14\-closeout.sh \-\-json\fR includes \fBdesktop_file_validate\fR; \fBpackaging/scripts/manual\-step14\-install\-smoke.sh \-\-json\fR includes \fBdesktop_file_validate_on_path\fR; test host after \fBapt install\fR both \fB.deb\fR files: \fBpackaging/scripts/manual\-step14\-install\-smoke.sh \-\-verify\-only\fR (optional \fBdesktop\-file\-validate\fR when \fBdesktop\-file\-utils\fR). \fBeditor/BUILD.md\fR, \fBdocs/PM_DEB_BUILD_ITERATION.md\fR; \fBdocs/PM_STAGE_MAP.md\fR STEP 14 (H6).
.SH OPTIONS
See
.BR le\-vibe (1).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/le\-vibe/
Configs, first\-run marker, welcome marker (\fB.welcome\-shown\fR), managed Ollama state,
\fBmodel\-decision.json\fR, \fBlock\-model.json\fR (concrete Ollama tag lock), \fBcontinue\-config.yaml\fR.
.TP
.I .lvibe/
Per\-project workspace memory \fBafter\fR consent on first open (e.g. \fBlvibe .\fR); see \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) and \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR le\-vibe (1),
.BR le\-vibe\-setup\-continue (1),
.BR codium (1),
.BR ollama (1).
Full docs: \fI/usr/share/doc/le-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
